Steps:
 # Select some text in the comments pane by mouse in SourceTree;
 # Press Cmd+C;

Expected result:
 * Selected text from the comments pane is copied to the clipboard;

Actual result:
 * The entire commit description is copied to the clipboard regardless of the selected text.

 

Possible cause:
 * The comments pane view does not become the first responder, the focus stays in the commits list pane, so Cmd+C copies the description of the currently selected commit.

 

Affected version: 4.0.1 (234)

{{Hello, I'm trying to close a release when I get this message:}}

{{fatal: could not read Password for '[https://xxxxxxxxx@bitbucket.org':|https://xxxxxxxxx@bitbucket.org%27/] Device not configured}}

{{Is there any workaround?}}

After pressing `Termial` button I see next message

"There was a problem opening this repository in iTerm2."
"An error occurred while trying to open iTerm2 with this repository. Please file a support ticket via the Help menu."

The same error happens with native Mac OS terminal

2020-01-15 08:46:03 +0000 (e) Error opening iTerm2 - {
    NSAppleScriptErrorAppName = Sourcetree;
    NSAppleScriptErrorBriefMessage = "Not authorized to send Apple events to iTerm.";
    NSAppleScriptErrorMessage = "Not authorized to send Apple events to iTerm.";
    NSAppleScriptErrorNumber = "-1743";
    NSAppleScriptErrorRange = "NSRange: {2042, 34}";
}

Mac OS: Catalina 10.15.2
Sourcetree: 4.0.1(234)
